• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –10,442,735.47

  Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities  
   = (–10,442,735.47) / (8,028,630.43)  
   ≈ –1.30  

Thus, the resulting ratio is approximately –1.30.
